Development Environment Setup
-----------------------------

1. Clone the project repository using git.
2. Install HomeBrew
3. Run "brew install gradle"
4. Run "gradle build" to run all tests and build a WAR.
5. Run "gradle jettyRun" to deploy using jetty.

IntelliJ IDEA Setup
-------------------
1. Run "gradle idea" to create the project files
2. Open the epic.ipr file

Installing CheckStyle-idea plugin
---------------------------------

1. Go to IntelliJ Idea Menu Bar -> Preferences -> Plugins  (Mac OSX)
   Go to File -> Settings -> Plugins (Windows/Linux)
2. Click on 'Browse Repositories' button
3. Search for 'CheckStyle-IDEA'
4. Right click on the plugin and choose install
5. Click Apply Button and restart IntelliJ
6. Look at the bottom left hand side whether there is a CheckStyle menu.

Please feel free to ask Erlangga or Chandru if you encounter any problems.

Setup CheckStyle-idea plugin
----------------------------
1. Go to IntelliJ Idea Menu Bar -> Preferences -> Plugins  (Mac OSX)
   Go to File -> Settings -> Plugins (Windows/Linux)
2. Go to CheckStyle menu
3. Click on add button and locate "checkstyleMain.xml" in the config/checkstyle folder inside the project
4. Check the file you just added and click on Apply

Extra Notes
-----------------
Please do "gradle build" before COMMITTING to the git repository. If the build failed, please DO NOT push your code
to the repository as it can break the build in the CI server.


